MediaRecorder.start_event \- MediaRecorder: start event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]start\f[B]\f[R] event of the \f[CR]MediaRecorder\f[R]
interface is fired when \f[CR]MediaRecorder.start()\f[R] is called.
At this point, the data starts being gathered into a \f[CR]Blob\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
